																		Nazi Wizards Fuck Off
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/greenwolf" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1814684); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1814684&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610163345" alt="GreenWolf" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1814684)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/greenwolf" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1814684); return false;" >GreenWolf</a></span> <span class="odate time_1528924183 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">13 Jun 2018 21:09</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3834815">
									

<p>Fuck Nazis.</p>
<p>I really wish this didn't need to be said, but nothing in this tale should be considered a reflection of my political views, nor should it be considered an endorsement of Nazi ideology. I have attempted to portray the evil, racism, and fanaticism of the Nazi regime with as much accuracy as is possible for a story about Nazi wizards plotting to assemble a doomsday weapon. I feel that to do otherwise would be to diminish the true horrors of the Nazi regime and a disservice to its victims.</p>
<p>Now, with that out of the way, some crit credits and some explanations. Thanks to my Doomcon teammates, NineVolt, ChaoSera, and sirpudding, for assistance in drafting and editing this piece. Thanks also to TyGently, Taffeta, and Conwell for reviewing and critiquing the draft.</p>
<p>This is my team's first entry in the Doomsday Contest, and is the start of an arc that involves Nazi wizards, ancient rituals, secret wars, a Golem that punches Nazis to death, and cursed swords. Stay tuned for the remaining installments, which will be posted later today and tomorrow.</p>
<p>The Obskuracorps is the occult arm of the SS Ahnenerbe. The Thule Society are an order of German oculists allied with the Obskuracorps in the Seventh Occult War. Both have been mentioned in passing in other works that reference the Seventh Occult War, but I believe that this is the first time they've been written about in detail. If you couldn't tell, they're bad people who want to do some really bad things.</p>
<p>The Allied Occult Initiative is the predecessor to the GOC, formed at the start of the Seventh Occult War to combat the Obskuracorps. They have also been mentioned in the past, but like the Obskuracorps, there are very few works that have delved into their history. They're a pretty eclectic bunch, but they're the good guys by default because they're fighting Nazis. The Foundation is not a member of the AOI, but does join the Seventh Occult War on their side following the D-Day landings.</p>
<p>SCP-4241 is a placeholder number until our team's skip is posted. It'll be changed to point to the skip once it's posted.</p>
<p>Edit: Holy shit, just noticed that I managed to typo the title of the page. Whoops.</p>
<h1><span>IMPORTANT NOTE FOR POTENTIAL TRANSLATORS</span></h1>
<h1><span>DO NOT TRANSLATE THIS WORK</span></h1>
<p>Given the political nature of this work, the ease with which it can be misinterpreted when taken out of context, and the reliance on specific and subtle nuances of the English language to convey a <em>very</em> specific message, I would respectfully ask that this piece <em>not</em> be translated into a different language. As is evident in the discussion below, it is all too easy for the intended nuance to be lost when traversing a language barrier.</p>

