															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/nederbird" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2854162); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2854162&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610163346" alt="Nederbird" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2854162)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/nederbird" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2854162); return false;" >Nederbird</a></span> <span class="odate time_1529266080 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">17 Jun 2018 20:08</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3839230">
									

<p>I think that's just Rabe grappling with the English language: it isn't his native tongue.</p>
<p>Though I believe he echoes a general sentiment throughout the German branch, where, from what I've understood, there's a great distaste for how Nazis are depicted in American media, particularly comic books and Hollywood, of which <em>Hellboy</em> is seen as a prime example. And since Obskura material often displays similarities to these, they're rather disliked over in DE.</p>
<p>Nazis and the Nazi period is generally a very touchy subject in Germany, as is expected to be handled with care. Not only are Nazis not to be glorified, but they are neither to be underestimated and represented as stupid or inept, as that would only obfuscate the frightening effectiveness and competence which allowed such an utterly dystopian system to come into being and persist. Moreover, the association of Nazis with magical occultism is generally seen as offensive among German as far as I know, as it serves to mystify them, on the one hand, and to trivialize the root of their horrendous atrocities to collusion with demonic or occult (and stereotypical) evil rather than attributing it to a very real and insidious, well-structured and thought-out ideology.</p>
<p>The writers of the SKP and 4R GoIs have been cautious in their representation of them so as to not obfuscate the very real nature and background of their evil, so to speak. I believe that that's what Rabe was alluding to.</p>

							</div>

								
					
