<p>I am indeed unfamiliar with Vietnamese and US anti-war propaganda. But I have never seen any US soldiers depicted as it is common for German soldiers. That's what I meant.</p>
<p>I'm looking forward to the last part then^^</p>
<p>I personally do not think that such crimes can be valued anyhow. Those tortured to death are tortured to death. It doesn't get any worse for them because their murderers are Nazis, Sovjets, CIA or some mafia thugs. Valueing their deaths serves only the living.</p>
<p>Therefore I prefer to leave the judgement completely to the reader. No slurs, no blurting out hateful phrases. I just tell the reader what happens or let the protagonist tell the story. With a neutral writing style the reader has to think, which apparently makes the experience much more intense and more intriguing as I am told, and the characters can bring in their actual emotions and thoughts.</p>

