				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-grom" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2026083); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2026083&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610163346" alt="Dr_Grom" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2026083)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-grom" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2026083); return false;" >Dr_Grom</a></span> <span class="odate time_1531472772 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">13 Jul 2018 09:06</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3872077">
									

<p>I think I can elaborate:</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>First of all, calling a German a Nazi is the maximum insult for most. So would I be as short tempered as a few years ago I would run directly to the harassment team and not even respond, at least not in a comprehensible manner. But I see that you are angry and feel misunderstood, so I refrain to do so. You don't know me and I don't know you. Implying a political stance to someone you don't know is not the best reaction I think, and I did not mean to imply you being close to US imperialism and to be honest I don't see where you've seen that implication.</p>
<p>Second of all I would like to point out that to me it seems obvious that Rabe's English skills are roughly at early beginner level and he is having big trouble to express himself. Mine also are not the best, so please keep that in mind when reading our posts and, if possible, when responding. Please interpret our postings in our favor. Nobody is threatening or insulting you.</p>
<p>Third, I am sorry for this, this is a big misunderstanding; neither Rabe nor me or anybody else mean any harm, nor is any of us a Nazi, not even close. Rather the opposite. Should you run into a DE user who you think is actually meaning harm, please report them to us. We can either elaborate possible misunderstandings or take measures if necessary. Should we encounter Neo-Nazis on DE we would probably remove them.<br />
And sorry for blocking your first post, we don't use to pin additional posts to the author's post on DE, so I assume Rabe didn't mean ill when he responded directly to your first post. This is not uncommon on DE. Once this is resolved I suggest that staff should delete this whole discussion to give you your first post back.</p>
<p>Regarding the SKP, there's no need to read machine translations, I am halfway through <a href="http://scp-int-sandbox.wikidot.com/dr-grom-s-sandbox-no-3">translating the hub to English</a>. That block in the German wiki is a bit older, in the meantime I've read everything tagged &quot;obskura&quot; despite a few SCPs. And to be honest, it was not easy to bring me to read through this series of articles. Not because they where bad, on the contrary, they are good. But because the concept of the Obskurakorps. I will go into detail about that later.<br />
I am aware that the SKP's concept is controversial, that is intended. I also expect a minor shitstorm every minute but I can deal with that. The reader shall think for themself. I don't want to tell people what to think, I just give them something to think about. I personally think that the reader is reached on a much more emotional level when they have to interpret an unvalued text. Readers have reported to feel uneasy when they read certain SKP-articles. That is the exact intended result. I think that the impact is much bigger when the readers see by themself that the Nazis where bad instead of telling them so, roughly spoken.<br />
That block is meant to prevent anyone from writing anything connecting both yet, as both are incompatible right now. Nothing else. If you find someone harassing you or your teammates because of that block, report them to us please. If you find the block rather harsh I can change it.<br />
I just have read these articles to get an own idea of what the Obskurakorps is, as I have only heard others experiences so far. I could have just taken that info and told everyone the OK/OC is just incompatible. I normally refuse to give feedback on EN because I perceive the environment and the way feedback is given and received here rather hostile. This incident seems to prove my perception. But instead of just declaring the OK/OC incompatible with the SKP I decided to try and do something about it, and as it is currently lacking a hub I gave my feedback on some of the articles about it. My goal is to find a way to make them compatible somehow.<br />
To elaborate the SKP's concept further: it is documentary. Of course every author writes differently but when I write something I think about the true reasons for the person to do what they do. Of course it is illegal to obey an illegal order and in modern armies you usually can legally refuse orders that go against your morale. But when you are getting shot if you disobey or you think you have no other choice it puts everything in a different light. When I'm writing SKP content, I put characters in exactly that situations and let them do what I think fits their personality. The reader then can judge the character. If you are interested in what exactly I mean I can link you to SCP-188-DE once its translation is finished, it is depicting that concept best.</p>
<p>I appologize if it sounded as if I was badmouthing your characters or storytelling or so. Indeed it is hard to get all nouances. I was talking about the whole concept of the OK/OC especially in your teams series which is the biggest work about them and thus IMO can be seen as the primary context of the Obskurakorps. Throughout the whole series I am painfully reminded of hollywood- and comic Nazis, like in Hellboy for example. As said, there is neither a GOI- nor series hub (or I didn't find it), so my feedback is scattered among multiple articles unfortunately. As Nederbörd (who FYI is no DE user) already pointed out, that concept is not always well perceived here. Of course there are also Germans who like that style, no doubt. I personally find that concept dehumanizing though. It is common to depict Nazis as just evil villains in this concept. By dealing with black magic, being incredibly arrogant, threatining all and everybody etc. But that is not what makes Obskura and the SKP incompatible, that are just different concepts of depicting Nazis. The problem is the power level especially in the following articles. During the war the SKP is researching rather &quot;worldly&quot; anomalies, with minor success. The Obskurakorps is researching rather &quot;unworldly&quot; anomalies. Normaly that would be compatible to each other and would be a nice hook for tales or so. But their power level is way too high in relation to the SKP. While the SKP struggles to get results and with Hitlers unwillingness to accept the existance of anomalies, the OK/OC and the AOI together mobilize the occult energy seemingly equal to the output of a nuclear power plant without problem. There are other things about Obskura that bother me, like the involvement of the 1925 disbanded Thule Society, but this is not the place to discuss that I think.</p>
<p>Regarding the Obskurakorps' name, I am totaly fine with Obskuracorps as a translation if it is kept in mind that it would be written with k in German. It's of course up to you what form you would like to use, but I suggest using one writing in all articles featuring them. I have a problem with the name itself but that chan't be changed anyway so I won't go into detail here, you find more regarding that in the HSA-008 discussion if you want.</p>
<p>Regarding my feedback in general, I'm just telling you my thoughts, you can do with that what you want. You can take it into account or ignore it, it's your article. I am offering you and your teammates my help, you can take it or refuse it. I do not intend to make any implications or get personal.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

